catalogue.definition: Calculated position of a target in Cartesian co-ordinates (two's complement form).
Track Mode-3/A code converted into octal representation.
Last valid and credible flight level used to update the track, in two's complement representation.

subitem.remark:
Note:
     The criteria to determine the credibility of the flight level are Tracker dependent.
     Credible means: within reasonable range of change with respect to the previous detection.
subitem.title: Measured Flight Level

catalogue.definition: Calculated Track Geometric Altitude Calculated geometric vertical distance above mean sea level, not related to barometric pressure.

subitem.remark:
Note:
     The source of altitude is identified in bits (SRC) of item I011/170 Track Status.
subitem.title: Calculated Track Geometric Altitude

catalogue.definition: Calculated Barometric Altitude of the track.

subitem.remark:

catalogue.definition: Ages of the last plot/local track, or the last valid mode-A/mode-C, used to update the system track.

subitems.name: PSR
subitems.title: Age of the last primary detection used to update the track

subitems.name: SSR
subitems.title: Age of the last secondary detection used to update the track

subitems.name: MDA
subitems.title: Age of the last Mode A detection used to update the track

subitems.name: MFL
subitems.title: Age of the last Mode C detection used to update the track

subitems.name: MDS
subitems.title: Age of the last Mode S detection used to update the track

subitems.name: ADS
subitems.title: Age of the last ADS report used to update the track

subitems.name: ADB
subitems.title: Age of the last ADS-B report used to update the track

subitems.name: MD1
subitems.title: Age of the last valid Mode 1 used to update the track

subitems.name: MD2
subitems.title: Age of the last Mode 2 used to update the track

subitems.name: LOP
subitems.title: Age of the last magentic loop detection

subitems.name: TRK
subitems.title: Actual track age since first occurrence

subitems.name: MUL
subitems.title: Age of the last multilateration detection

subitem.remark:
Note:
    The ages are counted from Data Item I011/140, Time Of Track
    Information, using the following formula:
    Age = Time of track information - Time of last (valid) update
    If the computed age is greater than the maximum value or if the
    data has never been received, then the corresponding subfield is not sent.
subitem.title: System Track Update Ages
